properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 7 at 3:30AM EST until January 9 at 1:00AM EST by NWS Mount Holly NJ
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 20 to 30 kt with gusts up to 40 kt and seas
3 to 6 feet expected.

* WHERE...The New Jersey and Delaware Atlantic coastal waters.

* WHEN...From 6 AM Wednesday to 1 AM EST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM WEDNESDAY TO 1 AM EST THURSDAY
